Task 1: Create Project & Push to GitHub

Objective: Create a simple User Registration Form and push it to a new GitHub repository.

1. Setup & Configuration

Open your terminal and run the following commands:

# 1. Create a directory for the project
mkdir question1

# 2. Navigate into the directory
cd question1

# 3. Configure Git (if not already done)
git config user.name "Your Name"
git config user.email "your_email@example.com"

# 4. Initialize Git repository
git init


2. Create the HTML File

Create a file named form.html.

gedit form.html


Code for form.html:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Event Registration Form</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Event Registration Form</h1>
    <form>
        <label>Name: </label><input type="text"><br>
        <label>Email: </label><input type="text"><br>
        <label>Phone: </label><input type="text"><br>
        <button type="submit">Register</button>
    </form>
</body>
</html>


3. Push to GitHub

Create a new repository on GitHub (e.g., named question01).

Run the following commands in your terminal:

# 1. Add the file to staging area
git add .

# 2. Commit the file
git commit -m "First Commit"

# 3. Rename master branch to main
git branch -M main

# 4. Link local repo to GitHub repo
# Replace <Your-Repo-URL> with the link from GitHub
git remote add origin <Your-Repo-URL>

# 5. Push to GitHub
git push -u origin main


Note: Use your Personal Access Token (PAT) as the password when pushing to GitHub.

Task 2: Branching, Modifying & Merging

Objective: Create a new branch, modify the form by adding a "Department" field, merge changes back to main, and push.

1. Create and Switch to New Branch

# Create and switch to a new branch named 'update-form'
git branch update-form
git checkout update-form


2. Modify the Code

Open form.html and add the Department field.

<!-- Added Field inside the form tag -->
<label>Department: </label><input type="text"><br>


3. Commit and Push Branch Changes

git add form.html
git commit -m "New Changes"
git push origin update-form


4. Merge to Main and Push

# Switch back to main
git checkout main

# Merge the branch
git merge update-form

# Push the merged changes
git push origin main
